# Uta Hagen's Questions on Abhayananda
(Contemporary Mark Antony)

###### Who am I?
I am Madhav Abhayananda, and I am 46 years old. I am a prominent television host, speaker, and journalist. I primarily discuss political issues, often putting forward my own ideals before others.

###### What time is it?
It is currently 9 AM on 10/10/2022 and it is quite hot in Delhi during this time. Thus, there is a loud fan behind me. During this time, there is political turmoil as a new president needs to be chosen for the party that I strongly support. (In line with the ongoing Congress elections.) I intend to use this as political momentum.

###### Where am I
I am currently situated adjacent to the main entrance of the Vighyan Bhavan in New Delhi. It is a popular location where many speeches have occurred, and through connections, I am able to speak here.
![Pasted image 20220930091826.png](data:image/png;base64,)
###### What surrounds me?
I am surrounded by many people that have crowded, as well as many cameras broadcasting this event. I am also surrounded by some of the other party members that assisted in the ousting of the previous president—I have to be diplomatic at the same time.

###### What are the given circumstances?
Abhayananda is in a very precarious position. The person whom he supports and the president of the party was just ousted due to blackmailing and trickery by Chirag and Birla. There are many people watching the television and Birla has tried to convince the people that the situation was for the best. If Abhayananda fails, he will be removed as a television host and will not be able to join the politics scene where he already plats an important role.

###### What are my relationships?
Despite being a television host, I play an important role in politics and I am not a supporter of Chirag and his ideologies.

###### What do I want?
I want to use this as an opportunity to ascend to power while denouncing the actions of Chirag and Birla against Jayshankar, and expose them. I do not want any public or party support for them, and will use this as an opening to wield more power despite being a television host.

###### What is in my way?
I need to be as diplomatic as possible when I deliver my speech and talk with others for my own safety; yet I need to find a way to convince the public to listen to me and protest against the actions of Chirag and Birla. I will use rhetoric, propaganda and other techniques to ensure the public is on my side.
